'''Kashiwa Shrine''' (柏神社, *Kashiwa‐jinja*) is a Shinto shrine located in 3‑chōme, in the area of {{ill|Kashiwa|ja|柏 (柏市)|lt=Kashiwa|lt_ja=柏|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Kashiwa City|ja|柏市|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Chiba Prefecture|ja|千葉県|12=draft|12=draft}}. It enshrines the deities of both {{ill|Haguro Shrine|ja|羽黒神社|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Yasaka Shrine|ja|八坂神社|12=draft|12=draft}}, and has long been venerated as {{ill|Gyūto Tennō|ja|牛頭天王|1=Gozu Tennō|lt=Gyūto Tennō|lt_ja=天王様|12=draft|12=draft}}. Its former shrine Ranking under the old modern system was that of a village shrine.

