{{see also|{{ill|Saijin|ja|祭神|12=draft|12=draft}}}}
; From Haguro Shrine
* {{ill|Tsukuyomi-no-Mikoto|ja|月読命|12=draft|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Ooyamatsumi-no-Mikoto|ja|大山祇命|1=Ōyamatsumi|12=draft|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Ōkuninushi|ja|大国主|lt=Great Land Master|lt_ja=大己貴命|12=draft|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Sukunahikona-no-Mikoto|ja|少彦名命|1=Sukunabikona|12=draft|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Ihitama-no-Kami|ja|伊氐波神|1=Dewa Shrine|lt=Ihitama-no-Kami|12=draft|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Ukano-Mitama-no-Mikoto|ja|稲倉魂命|1=Ukanomitama|lt=Ukanomitama-no-Mikoto|12=draft|12=draft}}
; From Yasaka Shrine
* {{ill|Susanoo-no-Mikoto|ja|素戔嗚尊|12=draft|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Kushinadahime-no-Mikoto|ja|稲田姫命|12=draft|12=draft}}

== History ==
Head priest: Tomono Toshimasa<ref>{{Cite web|和書|title=柏神社|url=http://kankou.kashiwa-cci.or.jp/spots/kashiwa-jinjya/|website=Kashiwa City Tourism Association|date=2016-11-15|accessdate=2021-11-01|language=ja}}</ref>

* The {{ill|Yasaka Shrine|ja|八坂神社|12=draft|12=draft}} was brought from the Yasaka Shrine of Gion-cho in {{ill|Kyoto City|ja|京都市|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Higashiyama Ward|ja|東山区|12=draft|12=draft}}, around {{ill|1661|ja|1661st year|12=draft|12=draft}} (1st year of {{ill|Kanbun|ja|寛文|12=draft|12=draft}}).
* The {{ill|Haguro Shrine|ja|羽黒神社|12=draft|12=draft}} was brought from the Haguro Shrine of the {{ill|Dewa Sanzan|ja|出羽三山|12=draft|12=draft}} in {{ill|Yamagata Prefecture|ja|山形県|12=draft|12=draft}} to Hakurodai in the local area, around {{ill|1660|ja|1660th year|12=draft|12=draft}} (Manji 3).
* In {{ill|1888|ja|1888th year|12=draft|12=draft}} ({{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|12=draft|12=draft}} 21) the Haguro Shrine was relocated within the shrine precincts.
* In {{ill|1907|ja|1907th year|12=draft|12=draft}} (Meiji 40) the Haguro Shrine was enshrined together with the Yasaka Shrine.
* In {{ill|1974|ja|1974th year|12=draft|12=draft}} ({{ill|Showa|ja|昭和|12=draft|12=draft}} 49) the shrine buildings were rebuilt and the name was officially changed to "Kashiwa Shrine" (the infobox parameter “name = 柏神社 | native_name = 柏神社” was updated), though the name of the religious corporation remains "Haguro Shrine".<ref>{{Cite web|和書|title=柏神社|url=https://www.pref.chiba.lg.jp/gakuji/shuukyou/houjin/kashiwa.html|website=Chiba Prefecture|accessdate=2021-11-01|language=ja|last=Chiba Prefecture}}</ref>

== Shrine Grounds ==
[[File:Kashiwa-jinja-fall-dec7-2012.jpg|thumb|Panoramic view of Kashiwa Shrine in autumn (2012)|alt=|500x500px]]

* Haiden (worship hall)
* Kaguraden (dance hall)
* Shamusho (administrative office)
* A giant ginkgo tree over 300 years old
